\crumbs
\h1{How to install gprof-exit}

gprof-exit comes with NO WARRANTY.

\h2{System requirements}
gprof-exit works only under UNIX.

This package implements an \tt{_exit} subroutine that writes profiling
information for
\a{http://www.gnu.org/software/binutils/manual/gprof-2.9.1/html_mono/gprof.html}{gprof}.

\h2{Installation}
If necessary, create a \tt{/package} directory:
<pre>
  mkdir /package
  chmod 1755 /package
  cd /package
</pre>

Download the gprof-exit package.  The most recent gprof-exit package is
\a{gprof-exit-\version.tar.gz}{gprof-exit~\version}.  Unpack gprof-exit in
\tt{/package}:
<pre>
  gunzip gprof-exit-\version.tar
  tar -xpf gprof-exit-\version.tar
  rm gprof-exit-\version.tar
  cd host/superscript.com/prog/gprof-exit-\version
</pre>

Compile the package:
<pre>
  package/compile
</pre>

Run some tests:
<pre>
  package/rts
</pre>
The output should be empty.

Install the package:
<pre>
  package/install
</pre>

Commands are installed in the
\tt{/package/host/superscript.com/command} directory.
For compatibility with prior versions, commands are also installed in
the \tt{/usr/local/bin} directory.

Report successful installation:
<pre>
  package/report
</pre>
</body></html>

